description: Sage Stossel, author of On the Loose in Boston, On the Loose in DC, and On the Loose in Philadelphia, is an Atlantic contributing editor and a cartoonist for the Boston Globe, the Atlantic.com, the Provincetown Banner (for which she received a New England Press Association Award), and elsewhere. Her cartoons have been featured by the New York Times, CNN Headline News, Best Editorial Cartoons of the Year, and other venues. Her graphic novel, Starling, was published in 2013.
name: Sage Stossel

description:
Peter Millar died in 2003 leaving behind a legacy of cartoons. His wife and daughter now maintain and preserve his website. He's best known for his work on CARtoons and DRAGtoons magazines. Apart from being an illustrator, cartoonist and avid dragon racer he's also a bronze sculptor usually sculpting western scenes. His sculptures sell for thousands of dollars. They range in height from approximately 12-18" and are limited in numbers. Usually not more than 300 pieces were made.

Millar is also known to use the aliasses Millarkey and Arin Cee. He co-created the CAR'toons magazine in 1959. He worked on the magazine untill 1963 after which he was replaced and began working on his own magazine called Drag Cartoons under his own publishing label called Millar Publishing Company. Though the releases of the magazine became more and more unfrequent he published his last Drag Cartoons #52 magazine a year before he died.
name: Pete Millar
